Design a program in java that identifies answer to the following questions.
(a) What is called first during an object creation, a static block or a constructor?
(b)? How many times each (a constructor and a static block) is executed
(c) Can we use non-static variables inside static methods? Why?


Answer a--> static block always executed first.
Answer b-->Static block executed once but the constructor are depend upon the how many object
are you calling.
Answer c-->Yes, a static method can access a non-static variable. This is done by
creating an object to the class and accessing the variable through the object